<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Ending With -ITY</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · Scrabble Words Finder</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -ITY suffix transforms adjectives into abstract nouns — complex becomes complexity, public becomes publicity. With Y worth 4 points, -ITY delivers 6 base points in just 3 tiles. Most -ITY words are 7-10 letters long, making them natural bingo candidates that score heavily even before premium square bonuses.</p>

<p>The combination of high base value, natural bingo length, and pairing with power tiles like X and J makes -ITY one of Scrabble's most rewarding suffixes.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -ITY Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">I(1)+T(1)+Y(4) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">400+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -ITY words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4–12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The Y tile's 4-point value makes -ITY one of the highest-scoring short suffixes in Scrabble. Only 2 Y tiles exist in the bag, so when you draw one, having I and T ready for an -ITY play is strong strategy. Words like COMPLEXITY (26 pts) and PROXIMITY (23 pts) combine X(8) with -ITY for devastating scores.</p>

<p>Even simple roots transform into powerful plays: MAJOR becomes MAJORITY (19), SCARCE becomes SCARCITY (15), GRAVE becomes GRAVITY (14).</p>

